snippet.textDisplay:
Just like there is a shortage  of lorry  drivers in the UK, we Sikhs will face a shortage  of Granthi's and Parcharaks in our Gurdwaras in the coming years.

The reason is that Granthi's are limited in how they can earn their income by Gurdwara committee members. Its a profession  that is not enticing the next generation to follow their Granthi parents because children see how they suffer. 

Some Granthis have turned into singers so they can earn more. We crave for keertan in happiness and sadness and need Gurbani all our life. A folk song does not give us the strength that a shabad gives.


We give thousands to folk singers. If only we value or own Granthi's in the same way, a lot will  encourage their children to join them.

Please do not just read this and forget about it. £10 given to a Granthi will be returned with divine blessings.
